            "content": "# TUI Improvements Milestone Plan\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-27\n**Milestone:** TUI Improvements\n**Status:** Planning\n**Recommended timing:** Between v0.5 (Sneakernet) and v0.6 (LAN Relay)\n\n---\n\n## Motivation\n\nPR #163 established the Action-based architecture (action channel, sync `update()`, background tasks). This was the critical foundation. But the code review against awesome-ratatui best practices identified several gaps in the UI layer that should be addressed before the TUI grows further.\n\nv0.6 (LAN Relay) adds relay status display, relay path visualization, and relay configuration — making the TUI significantly more complex. These improvements should land first.\n\n**Source:** `docs/analysis/2026-03-27-ratatui-ecosystem-analysis.md`\n\n---\n\n## Scope decisions\n\n- **Frameworks:** None adopted. All improvements are internal patterns or lightweight widget crates.\n- **New dependencies:** `ratatui-macros` (layout), `tui-popup` (popups). Both are first-party ratatui-org / core contributor crates.\n- **Not included:** Component trait (too large for this milestone), item-indexed scrollback (separate feature work).\n\n---\n\n## Issue decomposition\n\n### Tier 1: Zero-dependency fixes (immediate, high impact)\n\n#### Issue 1: Replace blocking `crossterm::event::poll` with `EventStream`\n\n`event.rs:36` uses `crossterm::event::poll(tick_rate)` — a **blocking syscall** inside `tokio::spawn`. This occupies a tokio worker thread for the full 100ms timeout on every iteration.\n\n**Fix:** Use crossterm's `event-stream` feature (async-native):\n\n```rust\nuse crossterm::event::EventStream;\nuse futures::StreamExt;\n\nlet mut reader = EventStream::new();\ntokio::spawn(async move {\n    loop {\n        tokio::select! {\n            event = reader.next() => {\n                match event {\n                    Some(Ok(CrosstermEvent::Key(key))) => { ... }\n                    Some(Ok(CrosstermEvent::Resize(w, h))) => { ... }\n                    _ => {}\n                }\n            }\n            _ = tokio::time::sleep(tick_rate) => {\n                sender.send(Event::Tick).ok();\n            }\n        }\n    }\n});\n```\n\n**Effort:** ~20 lines. Add `event-stream` feature to crossterm in `Cargo.toml`, add `futures` dep (likely already transitive).\n\n**Reference:** twitch-tui uses this exact pattern.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] `event.rs` uses `EventStream` instead of `event::poll`\n- [ ] No blocking syscalls in async context\n- [ ] All keyboard and resize events still work\n- [ ] `cargo test` passes\n\n**Blocked by:** nothing\n**Blocks:** nothing\n\n---\n\n#### Issue 2: Add `needs_render` flag (render on demand)\n\n`app.rs:1040` calls `terminal.draw()` on every `select!` wakeup — including `Action::Tick` and `Action::OutboxTick` which are explicitly no-ops in `update()`. At 10 ticks/second, that's 10 wasted draws/second when idle.\n\n**Fix:** Add a `needs_render: bool` field to `App`. Set it to `true` in action handlers that mutate visible state. Skip `terminal.draw()` when false.\n\n```rust\n// In run():\nif self.needs_render {\n    terminal.draw(|frame| ui::render(frame, self))?;\n    self.needs_render = false;\n}\n\n// In update():\nAction::Tick => { /* don't set needs_render */ }\nAction::Key(_) => { self.needs_render = true; /* ... */ }\nAction::SendComplete { .. } => { self.needs_render = true; /* ... */ }\n// etc.\n```\n\n**Effort:** ~15 lines. Add field + set it in each `Action` arm that changes visible state.\n\n**Reference:** tgt's `AppContext.clear_render_flag()` pattern.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] No draw on `Tick` or `OutboxTick` (when nothing changed)\n- [ ] All visible state changes trigger a redraw\n- [ ] Resize events always trigger a redraw\n- [ ] `cargo test` passes\n\n**Blocked by:** nothing\n**Blocks:** nothing\n\n---\n\n#### Issue 3: Add `ListState` to conversation list\n\nThe conversation list renders via `frame.render_widget(list, area)` — without `render_stateful_widget`, `highlight_symbol` and `highlight_style` are dead code. Selection can scroll off-screen with no auto-scroll.\n\n**Fix:** Add a `ListState` field to `App`, call `frame.render_stateful_widget(list, area, &mut state)`. Sync `ListState::select()` with `selected_conversation`.\n\n**Effort:** ~5 lines.\n\n**Reference:** Every reference app (tgt, nostui, rvIRC, iamb) uses `ListState`. This is not a best practice — it's basic ratatui correctness.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] Selected conversation is highlighted\n- [ ] Selection auto-scrolls when navigating beyond visible area\n- [ ] `cargo test` passes\n\n**Blocked by:** nothing\n**Blocks:** nothing\n\n---\n\n### Tier 2: Dependency adoptions (moderate effort)\n\n#### Issue 4: Adopt `ratatui-macros` for layout code\n\nReplace `chunks[N]` index access with named array destructuring across `ui.rs`.\n\n```rust\n// Before:\nlet chunks = Layout::default()\n    .direction(Direction::Vertical)\n    .constraints([Constraint::Length(1), Constraint::Length(3), ...])\n    .split(inner);\nlet title_area = chunks[0];\nlet id_area = chunks[1]; // wrong index = silent bug\n\n// After:\nlet [title_area, id_area, name_area, error_area, hints_area] =\n    vertical![==1, ==3, ==3, ==1, ==1].areas(inner);\n```\n\n**Targets:** `ui.rs` lines 32-44 (main layout), 305-312, 386-392, 441-453, 616-624 (popup layouts). 7+ layout blocks total.\n\n**Effort:** Moderate — touch every layout in `ui.rs`, but each is a straightforward mechanical replacement.\n\n**Trust:** First-party ratatui-org crate. Proc-macro, no unsafe.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] All `Layout::split()` + `chunks[N]` replaced with `vertical!`/`horizontal!` + destructuring\n- [ ] No numeric index access to layout results\n- [ ] Visual output unchanged\n- [ ] `cargo test` passes\n\n**Blocked by:** nothing\n**Blocks:** nothing\n\n---\n\n#### Issue 5: Adopt `tui-popup` for popup rendering\n\nReplace hand-rolled popup rendering (manual `Clear` + `popup_area_fixed()` rect math) with `tui-popup` widget.\n\nCurrently each popup rendering function manually:\n1. Calculates centered rect via `popup_area_fixed()`\n2. Renders `Clear` to erase background\n3. Renders a `Block` with title and borders\n4. Splits inner area with `Layout`\n\n`tui-popup` handles steps 1-3 as a single widget, reducing each popup render from ~15-30 lines to ~5-10.\n\n**Effort:** Moderate — 4 popup render functions to update. Each is mechanical.\n\n**Trust:** Maintained by joshka (ratatui core contributor). Part of `tui-widgets` family.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] All 4 popup render functions use `tui-popup`\n- [ ] `popup_area_fixed()` helper removed (replaced by widget)\n- [ ] Visual output matches or improves\n- [ ] `cargo test` passes\n\n**Blocked by:** nothing (but pairs well with PopupKind refactor from v0.5)\n**Blocks:** nothing\n\n---\n\n### Tier 3: Architectural patterns (higher effort, higher payoff)\n\n#### Issue 6: Component trait for panels and popups\n\n**Source:** tgt's `Component` trait, analysis Internal Pattern #2.\n\nExtract popup and panel state out of monolithic `App` into self-contained components:\n\n```rust\ntrait Component {\n    fn handle_key(&mut self, key: KeyEvent, tx: &mpsc::UnboundedSender<Action>) -> HandleResult;\n    fn handle_action(&mut self, action: &Action);\n    fn render(&self, frame: &mut Frame, area: Rect);\n}\n```\n\nEach popup, the conversation list, message panel, and input panel become `Component` implementations. `App` holds them as concrete typed fields and delegates to them.\n\n**Why:** `app.rs` is 1560+ lines with two `#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]` suppressions. The rvIRC analysis (22k-token `main.rs`) shows where this trajectory ends. v0.6 adds relay status panels, making the problem worse.\n\n**Scope:** Start with popups only (they're already isolated via `PopupKind` after v0.5 Issue D). Panels (conversations, messages, input) can be extracted in a follow-up.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] Each popup implements `Component`\n- [ ] `App.update()` delegates to components\n- [ ] `App.render()` delegates to components\n- [ ] No `#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]` needed on `update()` or `handle_key_event()`\n- [ ] `cargo test` passes\n\n**Blocked by:** v0.5 Issue D (PopupKind refactor)\n**Blocks:** nothing\n\n---\n\n#### Issue 7: Typed `BackendHandle` for async operations\n\n**Source:** iamb's `Requester` / `WorkerTask` pattern, analysis Internal Pattern #5.\n\nWrap `action_tx` in a struct with typed methods instead of inline `tokio::spawn` + `action_tx.clone()`:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct BackendHandle {\n    client: Arc<Client<TransportCoordinator>>,\n    action_tx: mpsc::UnboundedSender<Action>,\n}\n\nimpl BackendHandle {\n    fn send_message(&self, send_id: u64, prepared: PreparedMessage) {\n        let client = self.client.clone();\n        let tx = self.action_tx.clone();\n        tokio::spawn(async move {\n            let result = client.submit_prepared_tiered(&prepared).await;\n            let _ = tx.send(Action::SendComplete {\n                send_id,\n                result: result.map_err(|e| e.to_string()),\n            });\n        });\n    }\n\n    fn export_bundle(&self, path: PathBuf, filter: ExportFilter) { ... }\n    fn import_bundle(&self, path: PathBuf) { ... }\n    fn add_upstream(&self, url: String, transport_type: UpstreamType) { ... }\n}\n```\n\n**Why:** Currently `tokio::spawn` + `action_tx.clone()` appears inline in `handle_input_key()` (send), `handle_add_upstream_popup_key_event()` (upstream), and will appear in export/import. Each spawn duplicates the clone-spawn-send pattern. A typed handle makes the interface explicit and testable.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] All `tokio::spawn` + `action_tx` patterns in `app.rs` go through `BackendHandle`\n- [ ] `BackendHandle` is unit-testable (can verify action sent without real network)\n- [ ] `cargo test` passes\n\n**Blocked by:** nothing\n**Blocks:** nothing\n\n---\n\n### Deferred (not this milestone)\n\n#### Item-indexed scrollback\n\n**Source:** iamb's `scrollback.rs`, analysis Internal Pattern #3.\n\nReplace `message_scroll: u16` / `Paragraph::scroll()` with an item-indexed `ScrollbackState`. Enables selected-message (for reply/copy/forward), variable-height messages, \"load more\" trigger. Consider `tui-widget-list` as the rendering backend.\n\n**Why deferred:** Significant effort, no v0.5/v0.6 feature depends on it. Best done as a focused feature PR.\n\n#### `ratatui-toaster` for notifications\n\n**Why deferred:** 0.1.x, sparse API. `app.status: String` is adequate for now. Revisit if status stomping becomes a UX problem (multiple events overwriting each other).\n\n---\n\n## Dependency graph\n\n```\nTier 1 (zero-dep):    Issue 1 (EventStream)  Issue 2 (needs_render)  Issue 3 (ListState)\n                            (all independent, can be done in any order or parallel)\n\nTier 2 (deps):         Issue 4 (ratatui-macros)    Issue 5 (tui-popup)\n                            (independent of each other and Tier 1)\n\nTier 3 (arch):         Issue 6 (Component trait)    Issue 7 (BackendHandle)\n                            |\n                        v0.5 Issue D (PopupKind) -- prerequisite for Issue 6\n```\n\nAll Tier 1 items are independent. All Tier 2 items are independent. Tier 3 items benefit from Tier 1+2 being done first but don't strictly depend on them (except Issue 6 depends on PopupKind from v0.5).\n\n---\n\n## Success criteria\n\n- No blocking syscalls in async context\n- No wasted draws on idle ticks\n- Conversation list selection works correctly (highlight, auto-scroll)\n- No numeric `chunks[N]` index access in layout code\n- Popup rendering uses `tui-popup` widget\n- `app.rs` has no `#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]` suppressions\n- All async operations go through `BackendHandle`\n",
