conditional behavior\n\n| Method | Own | Relay |\n|---|---|---|\n| `outbox_get_by_content_id()` | Works | Never called (content_id is None) |\n| `outbox_get_for_recipient()` | Works | N/A (use routing_key) |\n| `outbox_get_maintenance_due()` | Returns Distributed entries | Skips relay entries |\n| `outbox_mark_confirmed()` | Sets Confirmed | Sets Relayed |\n\n### Relay-specific behavior\n\n- Deduplication on `(routing_key, message_id)` via unique index\n- Backpressure: configurable `max_relay_entries` + `max_relay_bytes`\n- TTL: `min(envelope.ttl_hours, relay_max_ttl)`. `None` defaults to `relay_max_ttl`\n- Loop prevention: `source_target` excluded from egress\n- Cleanup: `Relayed` entries cleaned up with shorter retention than `Confirmed`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Schema migration adds new columns without breaking existing data\n- Own entries work exactly as before (all existing tests pass)\n- Relay entries can be enqueued, queried, transitioned to Relayed, cleaned up\n- Dedup index prevents duplicate relay entries\n- Mixed Own + Relay entries coexist without interference\n\n## Requirements\n\n- #179 — TrustLevel + Contact rework (routing_key column in contacts)\n",
