            "content": "## v0.6: LAN Relay\n\nRoute messages through LAN peers during partial Internet outages. A node in Personal Relay mode accepts envelopes from peers, stores them in a relay outbox, and delivers via configured Quorum targets.\n\n**Design spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-28-v0.6-lan-relay-design.md`\n\n**Scope note:** This milestone is broader than the original ROADMAP description. It adds trust/contact rework, discovery hardening, crate extraction, and node operating modes as foundations for safe relay behavior. ROADMAP will be updated to reflect the expanded scope.\n\n---\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n- **Relay = outbox without crypto.** Same delivery state machine, no `inner_bytes`/DAG/re-encryption.\n- **Quorum-only relay in v0.6.** Node has no active peer discovery — relays to configured Quorum targets only. Direct-tier relay from nodes deferred to v0.7.\n- **`Relayed` terminal state.** Distinct from `Confirmed` (recipient ACK). Relay handoff = \"I got this to enough infrastructure nodes.\"\n- **Configurable trust-based policy.** `accept_from` + `relay_for` thresholds. Default: strangers can submit but not relay.\n- **Loop prevention.** `source_target` stored with relay entries, excluded from egress.\n- **Backpressure.** `max_relay_entries` + `max_relay_bytes`. Queue-full does not fail mailbox storage.\n\n---\n\n### Layer 0: Prerequisites (independent)\n\n- [ ] #179 — refactor: rework Contact model and add TrustLevel\n- [ ] #102 — security: enforce public_id on direct peers to scope Tier 1 routing\n- [ ] #116 — security: add channel binding to LAN identity challenge-response\n\n### Layer 0: Parallel (independent, not blocking relay)\n\n- [ ] #145 — feat(node): add mDNS discovery support for standalone node (advertise-only for v0.6)\n\n### Layer 1: Foundation\n\n- [ ] #205 — refactor: extract reme-relay crate (shared delivery engine) (requires #179, #102, #116)\n- [ ] #206 — refactor: generalize outbox for relay entries (Own vs Relay) (requires #179)\n- [ ] #75 — Discovery peer capability policy (requires #179)\n\n### Layer 2: Relay\n\n- [ ] #23 — feat(node): configurable node operating modes (requires #205)\n- [ ] #207 — feat(node): relay queue ingress (requires #23, #206, #75)\n- [ ] #208 — feat(node): relay queue egress (requires #23, #206, #75)\n\n### Layer 3: Integration\n\n- [ ] #209 — test: LAN relay integration tests (requires #207, #208)\n\n---\n\n### Dependency graph\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    subgraph \"Layer 0: Prerequisites\"\n        A179[\"#179 TrustLevel + Contact rework\"]\n        A102[\"#102 public_id enforcement\"]\n        A116[\"#116 channel binding\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Layer 0: Parallel\"\n        A145[\"#145 node mDNS (advertise-only)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Layer 1: Foundation\"\n        B205[\"#205 reme-relay crate\"]\n        B206[\"#206 Outbox generalization\"]\n        B75[\"#75 Peer capability policy\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Layer 2: Relay\"\n        C23[\"#23 Node operating modes\"]\n        C207[\"#207 Relay ingress\"]\n        C208[\"#208 Relay egress\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Layer 3: Integration\"\n        D209[\"#209 Integration tests\"]\n    end\n\n    A179 --> B205\n    A179 --> B206\n    A179 --> B75\n    A102 --> B205\n    A116 --> B205\n    B205 --> C23\n    C23 --> C207\n    C23 --> C208\n    B206 --> C207\n    B206 --> C208\n    B75 --> C207\n    B75 --> C208\n    A145 --> D209\n    C207 --> D209\n    C208 --> D209\n```\n\n---\n\n### Deferred from v0.6\n\n- Direct-tier relay from nodes (requires DiscoveryController extraction, v0.7)\n- `direct_deliver` policy axis (node needs active discovery first, v0.7)\n- `auto_direct_known_contacts` -> threshold migration (wider client config change)\n- ack_secret deterministic KDF (re-encryption for FLAG_DETACHED, v0.7)\n- BLE transport (v0.7)\n- LoRa/Meshtastic transport (v0.8)\n\n### Success criteria\n\n- Alice (no Internet) sends to Charlie (external) via Bob (has Internet + relay mode)\n- Message delivered when Bob's relay queue forwards to Quorum\n- Policy prevents Stranger peers from relaying (default config)\n- Node mode toggle works (Infrastructure vs Personal Relay)\n- Relay outbox persists across restarts\n- Duplicate submissions are idempotent\n- Source-target exclusion prevents echo loops\n",
