            "content": "## Summary\n\nEnable the standalone node to discover peer nodes on the LAN via mDNS and optionally use them for relay egress (Direct-tier delivery from nodes).\n\n## Background\n\nIn v0.6, node mDNS is advertise-only (#145). The node broadcasts its presence but does not discover or verify other peers. This limits relay egress to configured Quorum targets only.\n\nFor v0.7+, a Personal Relay node should be able to discover other nodes/clients on the LAN and deliver envelopes directly to them — the same way the client's `DiscoveryController` works today.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. Node subscribes to `_reme._tcp.local.` to discover peer nodes/clients\n2. Node verifies discovered peers via `/api/v1/identity` challenge-response\n3. Verified peers are registered as ephemeral Direct-tier targets in the node's `TransportCoordinator`\n4. Relay egress can now use Direct tier (deliver to discovered recipient) in addition to Quorum\n\n## Prerequisites\n\nThis requires extracting `DiscoveryController` from `apps/client/src/discovery/` into a shared crate (`reme-discovery` or `reme-relay`), since the same peer matching + verification + target registration logic is needed by both client and node.\n\n## Configuration\n\n```toml\n[lan_discovery]\nenabled = true\ndiscover_peers = true  # default: false (advertise-only)\nrefresh_interval_secs = 300\nmax_peers = 256\n```\n\n## Related\n\n- #145 — Node mDNS advertisement (prerequisite, advertise-only)\n- #23 — Node operating modes\n- #205 — reme-relay crate extraction\n- Client DiscoveryController: `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs`\n",
