            "new_string": "## v0.6: LAN relay\n\nRoute messages through LAN peers during partial Internet outages. Broader than originally planned — includes trust model, crate extraction, and node operating modes as foundations for safe relay behavior.\n\n### Contact trust model\n\n**Problem:** All contacts are treated equally — auto-created strangers from incoming messages are indistinguishable from manually verified contacts. Relay policy decisions need graduated trust.\n\n**Solution:**\n- `reme-contact` crate with `TrustLevel` enum (Stranger, Known, Verified, Trusted) and shared `Contact` struct\n- Schema v2 with persisted `routing_key`, `trust_level`, `verified_at`\n- LAN identity verification persists `Verified` trust state (was ephemeral-only)\n- Discovery filters to `Known+` contacts only (strangers visible in history but not eligible for direct delivery)\n\n**Deliverables:**\n- [x] `reme-contact` crate with `TrustLevel` and `Contact` types (PR #214)\n- [ ] Schema v2 in `reme-storage` (break-not-migrate, no ALTER TABLE)\n- [ ] Storage API returns `Contact` values instead of tuples\n- [ ] `Client` constructors take `Arc<Storage>` (explicit shared ownership)\n- [ ] Auto-create `Stranger` contacts from incoming messages\n- [ ] Manual add promotes existing `Stranger` → `Known`\n- [ ] Discovery persists verification as `Verified` trust state\n\n### Store-and-forward relay queue\n\nv0.6 introduces the **relay queue**, a generalized outbox for other people's messages. Same delivery state machine as the client outbox, but without crypto: no `inner_bytes`, no re-encryption, no DAG tracking — just opaque `envelope_bytes` → Quorum delivery.\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    subgraph \"Ingress\"\n        I1[\"v0.6: HTTP (LAN peer)\"]\n        I2[\"v0.9: + Meshtastic\"]\n    end\n\n    Q[(Relay Queue)]\n\n    subgraph \"Egress\"\n        E1[\"v0.6: Quorum (HTTP/MQTT)\"]\n        E2[\"v0.10: + BLE peers / Meshtastic\"]\n    end\n\n    I1 --> Q\n    I2 --> Q\n    Q --> E1\n    Q --> E2\n```\n\nEncrypted envelopes only, no decryption needed. Queue is persistent and survives restarts. Relay entries use a distinct `Relayed` terminal state (not `Confirmed` — that means recipient ACK). Loop prevention via `source_target` exclusion from egress.\n\nv0.6 relay is **Quorum-only** — the node has no active peer discovery, so no Direct-tier delivery from nodes. DiscoveryController stays in the client app.\n\n### Shared delivery engine (`reme-relay` crate)\n\n**Problem:** Personal Relay nodes need the same outbox tick loop (urgent retries, maintenance) as the client. Extracting shared logic avoids duplication.\n\n**Solution:**\n- `reme-relay` crate with `DeliveryEngine`, `TrustResolver` trait, `RelayPolicy`\n- `reme-relay` does NOT depend on `reme-storage` or `reme-encryption`\n- `Outbox` generalized with `OutboxOwnership` (Own vs Relay) and `Relayed` state\n\n### Node operating modes\n\n**Problem:** Different deployments need different relay behavior.\n\n**Solution:**\n- **Infrastructure** (default): Current fire-and-forget gossip replication. No outbox.\n- **Personal Relay**: Full outbox + Quorum delivery. Persistent relay queue with retry.\n\n### Peer capability policy\n\n**Problem:** Discovered peers need graduated trust for relay decisions.\n\n**Solution:**\n- Configurable trust thresholds: `accept_from` (who can submit), `relay_for` (whose envelopes we forward)\n- Per-trust-level rate limits\n- Backpressure: `max_relay_entries` + `max_relay_bytes` limits\n- Default: strangers can submit but not relay\n\n### Deliverables\n\n- [ ] `reme-contact` crate + Contact model rework (#179)\n- [ ] Security: enforce `public_id` on direct peers (#102)\n- [ ] Security: channel binding for identity challenge-response (#116)\n- [ ] Node mDNS advertisement — advertise-only (#145)\n- [ ] `reme-relay` crate extraction (#205)\n- [ ] Outbox generalization — Own vs Relay, `Relayed` state (#206)\n- [ ] Peer capability policy (#75)\n- [ ] Node operating modes — Infrastructure vs Personal Relay (#23)\n- [ ] Relay queue ingress — trust-based policy + HTTP response (#207)\n- [ ] Relay queue egress — Quorum delivery + loop prevention (#208)\n- [ ] Integration tests — 10 relay scenarios (#209)\n\n**Success criteria:**\n- Alice (no Internet) sends to Charlie (external) via Bob (has Internet + relay mode)\n- Message delivered when Bob's relay queue forwards to Quorum\n- Policy prevents Stranger peers from relaying (default config)\n- Node mode toggle works (Infrastructure vs Personal Relay)\n- Relay outbox persists across restarts\n- Duplicate submissions are idempotent\n- Source-target exclusion prevents echo loops\n\nYour message reaches the outside world through any peer that has connectivity, even if you don't.",
