          "text": "LoRa payloads range from 51B (SF12) to 222B (SF7). Let's see how far we can strip it down.\n\n## Current overhead inventory\n\nEvery byte that isn't content:\n\n```\nOUTER (plaintext routing layer):\n  version:          2B    — needed? version negotiation on LoRa?\n  routing_key:     16B    — who is this for\n  timestamp_hours:  4B    — when\n  ttl_hours:        3B    — how long to keep\n  message_id:      16B    — dedup\n  ephemeral_key:   32B    — per-message ECDH\n  ack_hash:        16B    — tombstone authorization\n\nINNER (encrypted):\n  from (PublicID):  32B   — who sent this\n  created_at_ms:    8B    — precise time\n  content:          var   — the actual message\n  prev_self:        9B    — DAG\n  observed_heads:   9B+   — DAG\n  epoch:            2B    — DAG epoch\n  flags:            1B    — flags\n\nCRYPTO:\n  AEAD tag:        16B    — integrity\n  XEdDSA sig:      64B    — authentication\n                  ─────\n  Total overhead: ~230B (with FLAG_DETACHED saving ~18B DAG → ~212B)\n```\n\nOn a 51B LoRa packet, that leaves **negative 161 bytes** for content. Even 222B gives you 10B. Useless.\n\n## The key insight: session keys unlock a completely different frame format\n\nWith an established Noise XX session, most of these fields become redundant — the session already binds sender, receiver, and key material. A LoRa-specific compact frame:\n\n```\nsession_tag:   4B    — truncated BLAKE3(session_key || \"reme-lora-tag-v1\")\n                       receiver scans active sessions for match\ncounter:       2B    — u16 monotonic (65K msgs per session, plenty for LoRa)\n                       doubles as: nonce, ordering, replay protection, message ID\nciphertext:    var   — ChaCha20Poly1305(key=session_key, nonce=counter_padded)\nAEAD tag:     16B    — Poly1305 (integrity + authentication)\n              ─────\nOverhead:     22B\n```\n\nThat's **22B total overhead**. Leaves **29B for content on 51B SF12**, or **200B on 222B SF7**.\n\nWhat was